summary:
Behind the Scenes of The Next Doctor (Part Six) 

Excerpt from David Bailey’s behind-the-scenes report in DWM #404 

  DWM: How...
caption:
Behind the Scenes of The Next Doctor (Part Six)

Excerpt from David Bailey’s behind-the-scenes report in DWM #404

DWM: How much do you consider these viewers who have been hooked by the revived show as ‘fans’, in the same way as the old grognards like you and I?

Russell T. Davies: I very much consider them fans. They are. That’s a fact. I think some journalists try to restrict the definition of fandom to male internet-bound merchandise-buyers, cos that’s an easy stereotype. And then, in turn, some fans like that, because they’d prefer to be exclusive. But the vast majority of fans welcome everyone in. Especially the kids, cos that’s the lifeblood.

DWM: As the first of five Specials, The Next Doctor marks the beginning of the end for both you and David. Are you even thinking about that yet?

Russell T. Davies: No, there’s far too much to do, there’s no time for sentiment! And I actually went straight from Doctor Who, to completely revamping Torchwood, with The Sarah Jane Adventures running at the same time, and then back to the Doctor… It’s just been constant work for me! And I wouldn’t have it any other way.

DWM: And finally: yes or no, have you decided yet how the Tenth Doctor regenerates?

Russell T. Davies: Yes, I’ve known for well over a year!
